      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SANTANA BOY (8) has a strong record this trip with five wins and three placings from 13 starts. Missed the frame latest (17.06) when fifth over 300m at this track in a Free For All. Appeals as a leading chance in this. ASTON FONTAINE (2) went straight to the front and never headed when winning two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 4th and beaten 6 lengths at Shepparton (22.12). Boasts a strong record from this draw with two wins and two minor placings from four starts. Should be about the money. WICKET (6) is a handy type who was well below best latest at Capalaba, finishing seventh (20.76) in a Grade 3/4. Generally a safe beginner but never in it last time. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Warrants plenty of respect. MIDNIGHT IN SALE (7) generally performs well over this distance.",
